</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drewcilla@themagicianstower>Drewcilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 8:34:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pet hold</span><hr size=1> get level 59, then get /pet hold .  <br>
<br>
<br>
then you will be allowed to have the pet out on raids.  Until then, don't count on it.<br>
<br>
Drewcilla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaereimmortalitis>Vaere Immortalitis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 9:01:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet hold</span><hr size=1> Depends on the area and if you have proven to your guild that you can controll your pet.  <br>
<br>
General rule is that if the mobs aoe, dont have a pet up unless you have /pet hold .   Otherwise its pretty safe.   So far I have used the pet in every zone in the game without pet hold. (PoP excluded as I am new there, also now I have pet hold its a lot easier.)<br>
<br>
Nice little trick is to get a Silverflank belt from CT, park pet someplace safe, and when battle is starting just summon it to you and send it in. Let the pet run back to its guard spot afterwords.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanbun>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 537<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 12:00:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .......</span><hr size=1> Without /pet hold, the only place I think it is dangerous to have a pet up is ToV. With it, there are several places where the mob's AE make it not worth keeping a pet up. The Planar Renewal heal might change that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2461<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 12:19:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets on raids?</span><hr size=1> Pets can screw with positioning though, too, and if you have a lot of mages on a raid pets can kill everyone by pushing a mob the wrong way.  Like mez-breakage, it's not much worse than melees, but it's harder to maintain control of a pet than your own melee attacks.<br>
<br>
If your guild is good at positioning it shouldn't be too hard to adjust pets into the mix, but the issue is still there and there are times when it's best to just kill your pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shadowmagildire>ShadowMagi LDire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 1:48:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Carefull...</span><hr size=1> Rule 1 of having pets on raids:  Never, EVER, for any reason let your pet out of your sight.  Doesn't matter if it currently has argo or not.  Pets aren't smart, pathing can suck.<br>
<br>
The problem with leaving your guarding out of site is that if your pet argos (maybe by pathing too close to another groups fight and getting AE'd) and gets killed you've just screwed your raid.<br>
<br>
A general rule of thumb is that if you don't have /pet hold, don't take pets on raids.  It is usually ok to use pets on big fights and then drop then afterwards.  I've seen a lot of good mages lose control of their pets.  You cannot back off a pet in battle very well.  You cannot watch your pet every minute on a hours and hours long raid.  The minute you turn your head you will get hit with a nuke or AE through a wall and your pet will take off down the hall.  Pets are great but they have a down side.<br>
<br>
<br>
Every mage fears this:<br>
<br>
Taunting attacking Master.<br>
You say to your raid, &quot;Has anyone seen my pet?&quot;<br>
Calming down Master..<br>
Calming down Master..<br>
Calming down Master..<br>
Calming down Master..<br>
You have no pet.<br>
You have no pet.<br>
You say to your raid, &quot;Umm, guys  something killed my pet, I think we have incoming&quot;<br>
Soandso tells your raid &quot;WTF did all this come from!&quot;<br>
<br>
LOL, thats happened to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moghedancarns>Moghedan Carns</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/starwars/lightsaber.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 2:03:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.station.sony.com/services/images/avacons/swg_logo_mb.gif hieght=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Carefull...</span><hr size=1> Uhmm...<br>
<br>
I might be wrong here, and I am just spitballing, but isn't that Rule 1 just a bit of the dumbassed approach?<br>
<br>
I mean, clearly, I do not go on huge raids in tough place as much as yourself, but it seems to me...  when you see &quot;Taunting Attacker, Master&quot;, and you are not expecting to see such, you either /sit /camp immeadiately, or you Gate and get someone else to CoH you back in.<br>
<br>
All of that depending on the danger level of the zone you are in.<br>
<br>
I mean, wouldn't gating and NOT being able to come back still be better than saying &quot;I think we might have incoming.&quot;?<br>
<br>
Someone tell me where I missed something. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243737"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~moghedan/pics/mogtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:Moghedan@Earthlink.net"> Moghedan@Earthlink.net</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
I was SK... but SK made me blue...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1174<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 3:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Carefull...</span><hr size=1> I personally would not want to disuade fellow mages from bagging their pets because they are not level 59, because they haven't yet invested the time in order to get /pet hold, since.. you know, basically only a handfull of mages at the upper levels are going to get that (ie: anyone over 59 will probably have, everyone else, which tends to be the majority, is screwed).<br>
<br>
My approach is more along the lines of.. learn how to control your pet, learn how to be attentive, and learn what to do if he does flee from your sight. These are better to know anyways, as /pet hold has to be consiously triggered, and if you fail to do so, and don't have these skills, then you're pretty much worse off than someone without pet hold and this knowledge.<br>
<br>
Myself, I don't have Pet Hold yet. 3.5 more AA, and I can start working on it. 8.5 more AA, and I'll actually have it. However, this has not stopped me from having a pet out around AoE'ing dragons. Nor has it caused the raiding parties I've hunted with to go &quot;Do you have pet hold? no? Ditch the pet!&quot; Amusingly, and your millage may vary, of course, but the raiding parties I hunt with actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>trust</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> me. Funny concept, I know. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I know when to have a pet, and when not to. I know when to summon one, and when to run without. <br>
<br>
That is, beyond one raid where, at that moment, my pet being out wasn't even an issue (traveling to the fight, pet was not even told to engage anything), and I was pointedly instructed to leave (Sorry, I went for the fight, I did not go, the only 55+ mage, to be a CotH whore). So I did. I saved myself having to CR out of Chardok <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=felagund>Felagund</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 3:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Carefull...</span><hr size=1> <br>
I am sure that the example given is just that, an example.  I been on a whole lot of large raids &amp; I HAVE lost a pet &amp; got that chilling message: &quot;taunting attacker master&quot;   This was before they made pets neutral of course.  <br>
<br>
What did I do??  Well,  as I remember I have done differnt things at differnt times.   Like... tried not to panic, sit, hit camp, attempted to mem gate, moved away from main force to die in place....  <br>
<br>
Today with /pet hold &amp; the pet not being KoS its much easier, but the stigma remains.  Pet's still get blamed for everything from trains to positioning.  My pet got blamed for positioning when I hadnt even sent him in yet.... blamed for trains when I didnt have one up!!<br>
<br>
My rule of thumb at this time is: multiple AE mobs (ToV), don't bother with a pet (unless its asked for by the raid leader).  Otherwise, the mages in my guild use them, watch them close, &amp; kill them when told to.  Pets are a pain in the neck with multiple AE mobs.  <br>
<br>
regards<br>
Felagund Inglorian<br>
<br>
<br>
