<br>
One, if your pet is someplace it shouldn't be and you send it to attack it could very easily argo mobs that it shouldn't along the way to the target.  I've seen this happen even after the pet faction change. <br>
<br>
Two, if you park your pet someplace out of sight can you guarantee that nothing will argo it?  No.  Most highend zones have at least 1 mob that have some sort of AE.  Many high end zones can have more than one raid occuring at once.  Can you promise that another raid or group will not fight near your pet and cause argo?  Not usually.<br>
<br>
If there are 60 people on a raid I'm not cocky enough to think that my pet is going to make a big enough of a difference that I'm willing to risk a wipe just cause I feel that pets should be allowed, even if the chance is small.  If you cannot take all reasonable steps to make sure you don't wipe the raid.. you shouldn't be on the raid.  Not having pet hold but inisisting on taking a pet through some zones or not keeping a close eye on your pet makes any mage irresponsible.  You can take chance solo, even in some groups.  You don't take chances on raids. Period.  There is no way to argo otherwise. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moghedancarns>Moghedan Carns</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/starwars/lightsaber.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 9:27:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7618.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.station.sony.com/services/images/avacons/swg_logo_mb.gif hieght=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets on Raids</span><hr size=1> Rogues shouldn't be allowed to use piercing weapons on raids, because they might take aggro from the main tank. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243737"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~moghedan/pics/mogtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
